*This project has been created as part of the 42 curriculum by jalsadik.*

# 🕹️ so_long

## 📌 Description

**so_long** is a simple 2D game built using the MiniLibX graphical library.

The objective of the game is to:

* collect all collectibles (`C`)
* then reach the exit (`E`)

This project focuses on:

* window management
* textures rendering
* event handling (keyboard input)
* map parsing and validation

---

## ⚙️ Instructions

### Compilation

```bash
make
```

### Run the game

```bash
./so_long maps/map.ber
```

---

## 🎮 Controls

```
↑  → move up
↓  → move down
←  → move left
→  → move right
ESC → exit game
```

---

## 🗺️ Map Rules*This project has been created as part of the 42 curriculum by jalsadik.*

# 🕹️ so_long

## 📌 Description

**so_long** is a simple 2D game built using the MiniLibX graphical library.

The objective of the game is to:

* collect all collectibles (`C`)
* then reach the exit (`E`)

This project focuses on:

* window management
* textures rendering
* event handling (keyboard input)
* map parsing and validation

---

## ⚙️ Instructions

### Compilation

```bash
make
```

### Run the game

```bash
./so_long maps/map.ber
```

---

## 🎮 Controls

```
↑  → move up
↓  → move down
←  → move left
→  → move right
ESC → exit game
```

---

## 🗺️ Map Rules

The map must:

* Be **rectangular**
* Be surrounded by walls (`1`)
* Contain:

  * 1 player (`P`)
  * 1 exit (`E`)
  * at least 1 collectible (`C`)
* Use only valid characters:

```
0 = empty
1 = wall
P = player
C = collectible
E = exit
```

---

## 🧠 Features

* Map validation (shape, walls, elements)
* Path validation using **flood fill**
* Player movement with collision detection
* Collectibles tracking
* Win condition handling
* Rendering using MiniLibX

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
includes/       → header files  
src/            → source files  
textures/       → game images (.xpm)  
maps/           → test maps  
get_next_line/  → file reading  
ft_printf/      → custom printf  
minilibx-linux/ → graphics library  
```

---

## 📚 Resources

* MiniLibX documentation
* man mlx
* 42 subject
* C documentation

### 🤖 AI Usage

AI was used to:

* debug errors (segfaults, logic issues)
* understand flood fill algorithm
* fix Norminette errors
* improve code organization

All outputs were reviewed, tested, and fully understood before use.

---*This project has been created as part of the 42 curriculum by jalsadik.*

